					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-592338#post-1622306</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-592338/scp-1970#post-1622306</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 20 Nov 2012 20:36:42 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>azzleflux</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1444699</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">I&nbsp;has&nbsp;a&nbsp;feedback.</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">This&nbsp;is&nbsp;my&nbsp;feedback.</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <blockquote> <p>Although SCP-1970 requires minimal security, it must be isolated from other anomalous objects.</p> </blockquote> <p>Shouldn't this be basic procedure for any object in containment?</p> <blockquote> <p>When SCP-1970 was not in operation it was possible to hear movement within the casing, as well as occasional breathing noises, including snoring.</p> </blockquote> <p>Are these little things really so loud that we can hear them breathing?</p> <blockquote> <p>However, due to his condition he was living alone and unable to convince any family members or caretakers that his television was &quot;filled with tiny, writhing men.&quot;</p> </blockquote> <p>Why not? Why couldn't he just show them?</p> </div> </div> </div> <p>Am I right to assume that the small organisms within the set were meant to originally act as a way to show images on a screen rather than using pixels? Anyways, I quite enjoyed it, but I really think the emotional impact is swift, fairly weak, and quickly forgotten about. +1 nonetheless</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
